@startuml concept_constellations
skinparam backgroundColor #FEFEFE
skinparam defaultFontName Monospaced
skinparam rectangleBorderColor #333333
skinparam arrowColor #2266AA
skinparam titleFontSize 18

title Digital Modulation — Constellation Maps & BER

rectangle "**BPSK**\n1 bit/symbol" as bpsk #E8F5E9

note bottom of bpsk
  2 points on real axis
  (−1, 0) and (+1, 0)
  Gray-coded: 0/1
  BER = Q(√(2·Eb/N0))
  Most robust, lowest rate
end note

rectangle "**QPSK**\n2 bits/symbol" as qpsk #FFF3E0

note bottom of qpsk
  4 points at ±1/√2 on I/Q
  π/4 rotation, 45° spacing
  Gray-coded: 00,01,11,10
  Same Eb/N0 as BPSK
  2× spectral efficiency
end note

rectangle "**16-QAM**\n4 bits/symbol" as qam #E3F2FD

note bottom of qam
  16 points on 4×4 I/Q grid
  Multiple amplitude levels
  Gray-coded per axis
  ~4 dB worse than QPSK
  4× spectral efficiency
end note

rectangle "**BER vs Eb/N0 Comparison**" as ber #F3E5F5

note bottom of ber
  Monte Carlo: 10000 bits/point
  Eb/N0 sweep: 0–12 dB
  mod_modulate() -> channel_awgn()
  -> mod_demodulate() -> count errors
  BPSK ≈ QPSK < 16-QAM (in BER)
end note

bpsk -[hidden]right-> qpsk
qpsk -[hidden]right-> qam
bpsk -down-> ber
qpsk -down-> ber
qam -down-> ber

@enduml
